trans poetic exchange arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery trans poetic exchange poets antonio cicero brazil jerome rothenberg us keijiro suga japan and frederic amat catalonia as well as video poet andre vallias brazil presented their work as part of the two day trans poetic exchange during his time as ambassador in india octavio paz 1914 1998 did double duty in the political arena he was the mexican government's official representative from 1962 until 1968 and in the literary world he successfully linked the eastern and western traditions his long poem blanco 1966 reframes mallarme's new constellar tradition found in un coup de des 1898 and mixes it with the erotic philosophy of the buddhist text hejavra tantra 690 twenty years later the brazilian poet haroldo de campos 1929 2003 penned a transcreation of paz's poem which he titled transblanco through the support of the stanford institute for creativity & the arts and the division of literatures cultures and languages artists literary scholars and poets from around the world met to discuss octavio paz and haroldo de campos's stellar literary relations department of iberian and latin american cultures michael rooney sica photographer 2009 2010 home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
